task.summary: Default task
Restore sun.java2d. Commit some finished classes.
Fix all classes in java.awt that were not previously buildable. Mark TODOs for remaining methods.
Stub out remaining peer interfaces. Extract SkinJobTextAttributesDecoder, which turns out to have uses outside SkinJobGraphics. Mostly complete implementation of SkinJobGraphics.
Apply a formatting standard. Purge unused imports.
Replace PlatformLogger with android.util.Log.
Delete make tools that should be unnecessary given the lack of native code in SkinJob.
Stub out more missing methods; fix more broken classes
Cleanups using Inspect Code; replace remaining native methods with stubs.
Fix more build errors (only 98 left outside tests!); implement SoftCache and font-related methods of GraphicsEnvironment; eliminate more dead code in sun.*
Remove dependencies of sun.awt.im.CompositionArea on Swing
Delete demos for now. (Some can be added back later, once we figure out which ones can use an Android app as an entry point.)
Fix all remaining compiler errors in src/share. Eliminate more dead code.
SkinJobGraphics now extends Graphics2D, giving it a more powerful interface.
Delete sun.java2d; migrate classes to use Shape instead of Region; finish SkinJobMenuPeer.
Delete sun.java2d; migrate classes to use Shape instead of Region; finish SkinJobMenuPeer.
Minor fixes
Add output folder to .hgignore
Delete make folder, since it's almost all specific to non-Android OSs. Delete upstream TODOs, since they're out of scope for SkinJob.
Remove dependency of DropTarget on Swing Timer. Extract timing magic numbers from DropTarget.
